title.narrative: New Element

description.narrative: A coordinated multisectoral response strategy based on risk and needs analysis, and a comprehensive approach to structural and emergency problems, allowed UNICEF and its implementing partners to provide access to critical emergency services in response to multiple crises to more than 733,000 people in WASH, protection, education, nutrition, health, and social protection in 80 municipalities in 13 departments. These efforts were implemented in coordination with key state actors, NGOs, and communities. Among the beneficiaries, 465,639;were children, who gained access to multiple essential services necessary for their development. Some 23 per cent of the total beneficiaries were women. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:26/01/2022
